- It's okay.

781
00:47:14,373 --> 00:47:15,707
Honestly, it's okay.

782
00:47:16,208 --> 00:47:17,750
Don't do this. It's fine.

783
00:47:17,751 --> 00:47:20,337
No, please spare me. I'm really sorry.

784
00:47:27,469 --> 00:47:28,428
Hyeong-ju.

785
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:33,600
Are you really okay?

786
00:47:57,958 --> 00:47:58,917
I'm sorry.

787
00:48:32,951 --> 00:48:34,869
If you don't want classes, don't come.

788
00:48:34,870 --> 00:48:37,581
If you don't want to study, then don't.
It's your life.

789
00:48:38,332 --> 00:48:39,166
But...

790
00:48:42,002 --> 00:48:43,629
don't get in someone else's way.

791
00:48:46,048 --> 00:48:49,676
Don't assume your minute
is the same as another person's.

792
00:48:50,969 --> 00:48:52,512
It may feel the same now...

793
00:48:58,477 --> 00:49:01,271
but later, it'll have made
decades of difference.

794
00:49:12,157 --> 00:49:13,200
Understood, you punks?

795
00:49:13,867 --> 00:49:14,701
Yes, sir!

796
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:17,370
Why are you guys silent? Understood?

797
00:49:17,371 --> 00:49:18,580
Yes, sir!

798
00:49:33,470 --> 00:49:36,473
<i>I will report
on the results of the ERPB's work.</i>

799
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:40,476
Through our inspector's efforts
at Guun High-Tech High School,

800
00:49:40,477 --> 00:49:43,896
the ERPB has resolved
violations of the right to learn.

801
00:49:43,897 --> 00:49:45,481
To prevent any recurrence,

802
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:49,860
we will take the following actions
alongside related departments.

803
00:49:49,861 --> 00:49:50,778
TATTOO REMOVAL CLINIC

804
00:49:50,779 --> 00:49:54,241
<i>From now on,
tattoos will be banned in all schools.</i>

805
00:49:55,117 --> 00:49:57,285
If you move,
your bare skin will get burned.

806
00:49:58,495 --> 00:50:01,957
<i>Motorcycles will be prohibited
on school grounds.</i>

807
00:50:02,457 --> 00:50:05,544
YOU'LL BE A GREAT MECHANIC
YOUR FRIEND, GEUN-DAE

808
00:50:11,299 --> 00:50:13,426
<i>Should a student join or attempt to join</i>

809
00:50:13,427 --> 00:50:17,513
<i>bullying gangs, school gangs,
or any organized crime groups,</i>

810
00:50:17,514 --> 00:50:19,306
<i>they will face adult charges</i>

811
00:50:19,307 --> 00:50:21,935
<i>and penalties under the law
on organized crime groups.</i>

812
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:27,356
Finally, we will work
with the Ministry of Justice and the MSIT

813
00:50:27,357 --> 00:50:30,359
to continuously take action on
millennial and Gen Z gangs

814
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:33,030
that recruit members through social media.

815
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:35,407
<i>We at the ERPB</i>

816
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:39,660
<i>will do our best to uphold
students' rights to compulsory education.</i>

817
00:50:39,661 --> 00:50:40,578
Turn off the TV!

818
00:50:40,579 --> 00:50:41,704
Yes, sir.

819
00:50:41,705 --> 00:50:43,456
Oh wow!

820
00:50:43,457 --> 00:50:46,084
You walked out of there,
and now you're here.

821
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:50,713
Minister, don't you think
you're on TV too much lately?

822
00:50:50,714 --> 00:50:52,548
Why? Do you want to be on it?

823
00:50:52,549 --> 00:50:55,468
That's not what I meant.
You just seem to be enjoying it.

824
00:50:55,469 --> 00:50:56,802
Am I not allowed to?

825
00:50:56,803 --> 00:50:58,179
Of course you are.

826
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:01,057
Did you see that?
"Those who disrupt learning, listen up."

827
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:03,643
"Don't get in the way
of compulsory education." So cool.

828
00:51:04,978 --> 00:51:08,939
May I interrupt your conversation
for a brief moment?

829
00:51:08,940 --> 00:51:09,857
What is it?

830
00:51:09,858 --> 00:51:13,944
While carrying out my duties recently,
I incurred a few expenses.

831
00:51:13,945 --> 00:51:15,905
Yes, you should claim expenses.

832
00:51:15,906 --> 00:51:17,115
What are they?

833
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:19,493
I was mugged

834
00:51:20,619 --> 00:51:22,328
about three times in total.

835
00:51:22,329 --> 00:51:23,955
Oh, mugged?

836
00:51:24,664 --> 00:51:26,457
They took 40,000 won in cash

837
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:29,794
and 500 won for premium coffee
at a vending machine.

838
00:51:29,795 --> 00:51:31,796
And outside the workshop,

839
00:51:31,797 --> 00:51:35,884
a pair of sneakers worth about 125,000 won
called Nike Air Force...

840
00:51:36,468 --> 00:51:39,595
Let's just say white Nike shoes
were taken from me.

841
00:51:39,596 --> 00:51:43,766
And I was microwaving
a 2,200-won Uiseong garlic sausage

842
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:46,102
at the school snack bar,

843
00:51:46,103 --> 00:51:48,187
and that was taken too.

844
00:51:48,188 --> 00:51:51,774
So I ultimately spent 167,700 won

845
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:53,943
from my personal funds.

846
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:57,197
Would I be able to claim those?

847
00:51:57,781 --> 00:51:58,657
Sure.

848
00:51:59,407 --> 00:52:01,450
Was anything else taken?

849
00:52:01,451 --> 00:52:03,245
Well...

850
00:52:03,745 --> 00:52:05,246
MEDICAL BILLS...

851
00:52:05,247 --> 00:52:06,832
No, nothing else.

852
00:52:08,041 --> 00:52:10,210
I see. Go ahead and claim the expenses.

853
00:52:10,794 --> 00:52:11,920
Thank you, sir.

854
00:52:15,924 --> 00:52:17,300
Should I buy you a sausage?

855
00:52:18,135 --> 00:52:20,344
Pardon? No, sir.

856
00:52:20,345 --> 00:52:23,681
- It's fine.
- Have one of those Uiseong garlic things.

857
00:52:23,682 --> 00:52:24,766
- Go on.
- Hey.

858
00:52:25,517 --> 00:52:26,350
He's just a kid.

859
00:52:26,351 --> 00:52:29,020
- But he said he had it taken--
- That's enough.

860
00:55:16,938 --> 00:55:19,899
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim
